Hi, excellent article, but I have one question.  
I see, this is all on one form. I have situation, where winforms gui I have in other asssembly and I want to update progress bar using a delegate/event. So I added  
public delegate void NotifyAboutIterationEnd(int iteration);  
public event NotifyAboutIterationEnd Notify;  
and in the presenter   
algorithm.Notify +=new NotifyAboutIterationEnd( UpdateProgressBar);  
Unfortunatelly this doesn't work and I an't debug why.

You could also pass the uiTaskScheduler to the task and report progress by starting a task on the uiTaskScheduler, along these lines:  

 TaskScheduler uiTaskScheduler = TaskScheduler.FromCurrentSynchronizationContext();  
 System.Threading.Tasks.Task.Factory  
 .StartNew(() => TheTask(uiTaskScheduler))  
 .ContinueWith(...);  

 private void TheTask(TaskScheduler uiTaskScheduler)  
 {  
 ...  
 // Report status  
 if (uiTaskScheduler != null)  
 System.Threading.Tasks.Task.Factory.StartNew(() => ReportProgress(pct), null, CancellationToken.None, TaskCreationOptions.None, uiTaskScheduler);   
 ...  
 }

What remains unclear is how the backgroundworker is going report progress deep inside the object graph. Should I pass the reference?

